<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Song of Solomon on Christian Internet Resources</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/</link><description>Recent content in Song of Solomon on Christian Internet Resources</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Song of Solomon 1</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-01/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-01/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-1">Song of Solomon Chapter 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in'>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'> 1&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family: "Times New Roman",serif'>:&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Solomon’s Song of Songs&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Bride
&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;b>&lt;sup>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  &lt;span style='color:#C00000'>2&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/sup>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>“Please kiss me! Your love is better than wine.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>Your anointing oils have a pleasing fragrance;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                  your name is like purified oil;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                  that’s why young women love you.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 2</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-02/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-02/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-2">Song of Solomon Chapter 2&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>“I’m a rose of Sharon, a lily of the valley.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Groom&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“My darling among young women is&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  like a lily among thorns.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Bride&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v3" id="v3">&lt;sup class="verse-num">3&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height: 115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>“My beloved among young men is&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                        like an apricot tree in the forest.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 3</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-03/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-03/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-3">Song of Solomon Chapter 3&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>“In bed night after night I sought the one I love;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>                              I looked for him but didn’t find him.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>                        &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height: 115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>‘I need to get up and look around the city;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>                              in the streets and squares&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#C00000'>                                    I have to find the one I love.’&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 4</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-04/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-04/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-4">Song of Solomon Chapter 4&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“You are so beautiful, my darling;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  you’re so beautiful!&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  Your eyes are like doves behind your veil;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  your hair is like a flock of goats&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        coming down Mount Gilead.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Your teeth are like a flock of shorn ewes&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  that have come up from their washing,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 5</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-05/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-5">Song of Solomon Chapter 5&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“I’ve come to my garden, &lt;b>my sister, my bride&lt;/b>;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        I’ve gathered my myrrh and spice.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  I’ve eaten my honey and honeycomb,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        and drunk my wine and milk.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  Eat, friends, and drink;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        drink deeply, lovers.”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%; font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                                     &lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>S of S 5:1&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 6</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-06/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-06/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-6">Song of Solomon Chapter 6&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt; line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#00B050'>“Where has your beloved gone,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#00B050'>                        most beautiful among women?&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#00B050'>                  Where has he turned&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#00B050'>                        so we can help you find him?”&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Bride           &lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height: 115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#00B050'>“He’s gone down to his garden, to the beds of spices,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#00B050'>                  to pasture his flock in the gardens and gather lilies.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 7</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-07/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-07/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-7">Song of Solomon Chapter 7&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span class="verse verse-v1" id="v1">&lt;sup class="verse-num">1&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>“Your feet are so graceful in sandals, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        prince’s daughter!&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  The curves of your hips are like jewels, &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        the work of an artist’s hand.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Your navel is like a round goblet&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                        that’s always full of mixed wine;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>                  your stomach is like a pile of wheat&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Song of Solomon 8</title><link>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-08/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/translations/cnt-ot/song-of-solomon/chapter-08/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="song-of-solomon-chapter-8">Song of Solomon Chapter 8&lt;/h2>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;b>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>         &lt;span style='color:#C00000'>8&lt;sup>:1&lt;/sup>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>“Oh that you were my brother,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                        who nursed at my mother’s breasts.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                  If I found you outdoors, I’d kiss you;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                        and nobody would despise me.&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>            &lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;span class="verse verse-v2" id="v2">&lt;sup class="verse-num">2&lt;/sup> &lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>I’d take you into my mother’s house,&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-top:0in;margin-bottom: 0in;margin-left:0in;'>&lt;i>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif; color:#C00000'>                        who used to instruct me;&lt;/span>&lt;/i>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>